<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Andreas Voit von Rieneck, Amtmann zu Karlsburg und Karlstadt</head><p>Der Rat übersendet einen offenen Brief von Wilhelm und Wiguläus von Wolfstein wegen des vor letzter Weihnacht übersandten Pferds, das nicht dem Adressaten gehört.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_373" id="185v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_373_r2l22">Andres vogt von Ryneck / <expan>amptm<ex>an</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l23">ʒu karlburg vnd karlſtat </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l24"><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan> Andres als Jr vns
                                <expan>verſchr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt / daʒ das pfeͣrd / daʒ wır </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l25">eẅch nehſt vor <expan>weyhenn<ex>achten</ex></expan>
                        bey <expan>eẅ<ex>r</ex>m</expan> knecht <expan>ſchıkte<ex>n</ex></expan> .
                        eẅr pferd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l26">nıht ſey daʒ Jr ʒu Beheım
                            <expan>v<ex>er</ex>lorn</expan> habt / vnd
                            <expan>ſchreıbe<ex>n</ex></expan> . eẅch ~ dıe </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l27"><expan>vom<ex>m</ex></expan> wolfſtein als ſıe
                        pıllıch <expan>ſülle<ex>n</ex></expan> ſo wellt Jr vns das </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l28">pfeͣrd <expan>wıd<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>ſchık<ex>en</ex></expan> etc / das haben wır wol
                                <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> / Vnd </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l29">haben mıt <expan>h<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>wılhelm<ex>m</ex></expan> vnd <expan>h<ex>er</ex>n</expan> wygeleıs
                                <expan>vom<ex>m</ex></expan> wolfſtein </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l30">
<add><expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan></add> dauon geredt / dıe haben vns geſagt
                        / wıe ſıe nehſt in </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_373_r2l31">ırem brıef von der ſache
                            <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> geſchrıben haben <add><ab facs="#facs_373_r2l32">des ſıe gnug deẅht </ab></add> wıe
                                <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan>
</ab>
<pb facs="#facs_374" id="186r"/>
<ab facs="#facs_374_r1l1">ſo ſchreıben ſıe <expan>yecʒ<ex>unden</ex></expan>
<expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan> darumb als Jr in ırem
                            <expan>offen<ex>en</ex></expan> brıef eẅch hıe = </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_374_r1l2">mit geſandt / wol <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan>
<expan>w<ex>er</ex>det</expan> / <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ıa</expan> ııȷ<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>fabıa<ex>n</ex>ȷ</expan> et <expan>ſebaſtıa<ex>n</ex>ȷ</expan>
</ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_373" id="185v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Andres Vogt von Ryneck, <expan>amptm<ex>an</ex></expan> zu Karlburg und
                        Karlstat </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan> Andres, als ir uns <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt, daz
                        das pfeͣrd, daz wir ewch nehst vor <app>
<note><q type="date"><expan>weyhenn<ex>achten</ex></expan></q>25.12.1421</note>
</app> bey <expan>ew<ex>r</ex>m</expan> knecht
                            <expan>schikte<ex>n</ex></expan>, ewr pferd niht sey, daz ir zu Beheim
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>lorn</expan> habt, und
                            <expan>schreibe<ex>n</ex></expan> ewch die <expan>vom<ex>m</ex></expan>
                        Wolfstein, als sie pillich <expan>sülle<ex>n</ex></expan>, so wellt ir uns
                        das pfeͣrd <expan>wid<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>schik<ex>en</ex></expan> etc., das haben wir wol
                                <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan> und haben mit
                            <expan>h<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<expan>Wilhelm<ex>m</ex></expan> und <expan>h<ex>er</ex>n</expan> Wygeleis
                                <expan>vom<ex>m</ex></expan> Wolfstein
                                <add><expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan></add> davon geredt, die haben uns
                        gesagt, wie sie nehst in irem brief von der sache
                            <expan>weg<ex>en</ex></expan> geschriben haben, <add>des sie gnug
                            dewht</add>, wie <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan>
<pb facs="#facs_374" id="186r"/>so schreiben sie <expan>yecz<ex>unden</ex></expan>
<expan>ab<ex>er</ex></expan> darumb, als ir in irem
                            <expan>offen<ex>en</ex></expan> brief ewch hiemit gesandt wol
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>nemen</expan>
<expan>w<ex>er</ex>det</expan>. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> iii<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>Fabia<ex>n</ex>i</expan> et <expan>Sebastia<ex>n</ex>i</expan>.</ab>
</div>
</div></body>
